President Barack Obama has proclaimed November 20 through November 26, 2011, as National Family Week. In his proclamation, he highlights the importance of American families and the love and unity that binds them together. The administration is committed to supporting families by investing in early learning programs, education reform, and making higher education more affordable. The President also acknowledges the contributions and sacrifices of service members and their families and encourages Americans to make a difference in their lives through initiatives like Joining Forces. As the holiday season approaches, President Obama urges everyone to give thanks to their loved ones and work together to achieve their highest ambitions. The proclamation calls on all states, communities, and individuals to observe National Family Week with appropriate ceremonies and activities.